post_text:
POUSD will be closed on Monday, 10/28 and Tuesday 10/29. Most of our teachers and staff are evacuated and we do not know when they will be allowed to return. Also, the Kincade fire is at this time only 10% contained and has grown 30,000 acres.

Moreover, while the current PSPS is projected to end on Monday, PG&E will then need time to inspect and repair lines before reenergizing. Given the high winds and fire damage around the county, this could take a while.

A decision will be made about Wednesday on Tuesday, or earlier if conditions warrant. PSPS, air-quality, availability of staff, and the readiness of district facilities all play a part in the decision about when to reopen school.

The Governing Board of the Piner-Olivet Union School District has selected Dr. Rick Brewer and Dr. Wendell Chun of Education Leadership Services as its advisors to assist the Board in its search for a new superintendent. One of the first tasks in the search and selection process is to determine the specific traits, skills, abilities, and experience desired in the new superintendent. The Board feels it is important to obtain input from others.
Written comments may be made on survey questionnaire forms available at the district office, or you can complete the survey on line by going to: http://bit.ly/pousdsuptsurvey. Please submit survey responses by July 8, 2016.

post_text:
The Governing Board of the Piner-Olivet Union School District has selected Dr. Rick Brewer and Dr. Wendell Chun of Education Leadership Services as its advisors to assist the Board in its search for a new superintendent. One of the first tasks in the search and selection process is to determine the specific traits, skills, abilities, and experience desired in the new superintendent. The Board feels it is important to obtain input from others. They would like to invite members of the staff and community to meet with Dr. Brewer on June 27th and June 28th to offer what they consider to be the criteria desired in the new superintendent.

Appointments can be made by calling Cathy Manno at 522-3000 to schedule an appointment. Written comments may be made on survey questionnaire forms available at the district office, or you can complete the survey on line by going to: http://bit.ly/pousdsuptsurvey.

El Consejo Directivo del Distrito Escolar de Piner-Olivet Union School District ha seleccionado al Dr. Rick Brewer de “Servicios de Liderazgo Educacional” como su asesor para ayudar al Consejo en la búsqueda de un nuevo Superintendente. Una de las primeras tareas en el proceso de búsqueda y selección es determinar las características específicas, habilidades y experiencia deseada en el nuevo superintendente. Parents, please read this important announcement: A federal judge has ordered the California Department of Education (CDE) to disclose personal student information – including documents and data dating back to 2008 – to the plaintiffs who initiated an ongoing lawsuit against the state agency.
The court allows parents or students to file an objection, and the CDE is requesting that Local Educational Agencies (LEAs) post this link with information about the litigation on their websites: http://www.cde.ca.gov/re/di/ws/morganhillcase.asp

Read more in the SCOE press release: http://scoe.org/pub/htdocs/news-archive.html?news_id=780

CDE.CA.GOV
Objections to Disclosure of Student Records - Web Site Information (CA Dept of Education)

Our district, in partnership with the Sonoma County Office of Education, will be hosting a screening of this thought provoking film on August 24th at the 3rd Street Cinema, 620 Third Street, Santa Rosa. Doors open at 5:30 pm. Showtime is at 6:00 pm.

post_text:
Spring is here and there is a creative, energetic bustle permeating the Northwest Prep campus with students actively creating project pieces as a culmination of their project work. We know that one of the highest forms of learning involves creation and as part of our philosophy of creating opportunities for deeper learning, students are creating museum pieces, documentaries, short films, interactive games, puzzles, and other pieces of evidence which will be on display at our Spring Academic Exhibition on April 9th at 5:30 p.m.

All are invited to join us in this celebration of student learning! Invite friends and family to this event where students will showcase their work in the Multipurpose Room at the school.

http://www.northwestprep.org/
